alidate error rate,\npending requests, database load, and connection acquisition latency. Keep rollback instructions\navailable and do not automatically change production configuration.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_knowledge_9a3152d0d6c37f2922e69841"], "timestamp": "2026-06-01T01:00:00Z"}, {"description": "Section: Resolution and learning\nAfter human review, the team restored the validated limit and confirmed database load remained\nsafe. The release checklist now requires a connection limit diff and a pending-request comparison.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_knowledge_097c2100c2d57d67cba31abd"], "timestamp": "2026-06-28T06:30:00Z"}, {"description": "Section: Root cause\nA configuration rollout reduced the payment-service database connection limit below the validated\nproduction baseline. The pool saturated and repository operations waited for connection acquisition.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_knowledge_4d8e764efe20840aeb107733"], "timestamp": "2026-06-28T06:30:00Z"}, {"description": "Section: Impact\nCheckout requests returned elevated errors and connection pool timeout messages. Gateway latency\nremained within its normal range.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_knowledge_5098b4793a04a998d5fa138c"], "timestamp": "2026-06-28T06:30:00Z"}, {"description": "A release 3 minutes before the incident changed db.pool.max_connections from 50 to 5.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_payment_change_pool_limit"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T10:17:00+08:00"}, {"description": "payment-service directly depends on postgres-primary and payment-gateway.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_payment_topology_dependencies"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T10:20:00+08:00"}, {"description": "All 5 configured database connections were active while 37 requests waited.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_payment_metric_pool_saturation"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T10:21:00+08:00"}, {"description": "payment-service could not acquire a database connection within 5 seconds.", "evidence_ids": ["ev_payment_log_pool_timeout"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T10:23:12+08:00"}, {"